[2]
Date: 12 Apr 2000
From: SLAMA, Dr G. (KIR) <slamag@tskl.net.ki>
Via: Pacific Public Health Surveillance Network <pacnet@idefix.spc.int>

This is the information obtained this morning from Dr Airam Metai,
Permanent Secretary for Health.
Hepatitis outbreak among borders at Kouma High School on Abemama island
(Central District, Gilbert group) was reported on 6 Apr 2000. The District
Principal Nursing Officer flew to Abemama on 9 Apr 2000 to carry out an
investigation and hepatitis B vaccination. She will be coming back on 14
Apr 2000 with hopefully more details and blood samples for laboratory
investigation. At the moment the [Ministry of Health] hasn't got exact
numbers of persons affected.
More details will be provided once available.
--
Dr George Slama
